news.title: Smartworks leases 450,000 sq ft office space in Hyderabad
news.para: Smartworks has been lapping up office spaces across the country, with demand from enterprises driving the growth. The firm has added more than a million sq ft in 2021, with plans to double it in 2022.

news.title: Ludhiana civic body rejects proposal to take over 18 colonies from GLADA
news.para: ​The proposal was dropped when some of the councillors, who represent these localities, demanded for the same while saying that Glada had funds for development works and it will be better if MC does not take over these colonies as of now.

news.title: Haryana to give one-time waiver on payment of interest of pending property tax
news.para: ​This decision will benefit about 18.80 lakh property tax payers of the state which includes residential, commercial, industrial institutions, he said, while adding that a proposal in this regard has been approved by Chief Minister Manohar Lal Khattar.

news.title: Panvel civic body accepts Cidco's proposal to handover physical infra
news.para: The handover of services has been agreed upon with effect from January 1, 2022. It was decided to ink the agreement for handover of services, in the meeting between Cidco and Panvel civic officials held on December 27.

news.title: Chennai: Anna University experts begin inspecting TNUHDB building
news.para: The Tamil Nadu Urban Habitat Development Board (TNUHDB), formerly the Tamil Nadu Slum Clearance Board, has also ordered inspection all its buildings in the city that are more than 25 years old - 17,734 - before Friday. Those deemed dangerous would be demolished.

news.title: DTCP to conduct fresh survey of guesthouses in Gurugram
news.para: Deputy commissioner Yash Garg held a task force meeting on Tuesday and discussed issues related to mushrooming of illegal guesthouses in the city.

news.title: South Delhi civic body to regularise illegal constructions in shops at fixed rate
news.para: This will generate good revenue for the civic body and allow shopkeepers to have a clear title of the commercial property that will reduce their unnecessary harassment, said officials.

news.title: Pune civic body to levy property tax in 23 merged villages, residents demur
news.para: Around 1.6lakh properties will be added in the tax ambit of Pune Municipal Corporation (PMC). On Tuesday, the civic standing committee approved a proposal regarding the same.

news.title: Navi Mumbai: Demolished illegal buildings rise again in Nerul, Belapur wards
news.para: The illegal Nerul building was demolished in 2016 by the then civic chief, Tukaram Mundhe. The Darave building was demolished last year. Civic officials had also displayed notices at these sites that the illegal structures have been demolished.

news.title: Gurugram: Two illegal colonies demolished in DTCP drive
news.para: The district town planner had earlier issued showcause notices to builders of these illegal colonies, but the construction was being carried out.

news.title: BMC lost Rs 2,000 crore due to unchanged property tax in Mumbai: Minister
news.para: After he pointed out that the state had not yet waived property tax for dwellings below 500 square feet in the city in accordance with the Shiv Sena’s election promise, Shinde said this was under consideration, and the state would soon take a decision.

news.title: Karnataka government assures B to A khata transfer
news.para: In the year 2021-22, holders of 13,56,087 properties paid tax under self-declaration of property tax. Among these, 97,057 are commercial buildings, 9,112 multi-storey buildings and 12,59,030 are residential buildings.

news.title: Mumbai: Film producer Sanghvi held for yet another housing scam
news.para: On Monday, the Housing unit of EOW took custody of Sanghvi from the Arthur Road jail in connection with a 2018 cheating case. The court gave the police one day’s custody and then, on Tuesday, again sent him to judicial custody.

news.title: Sebi board tightens rules for utilisation of IPO proceeds
news.para: ​The regulator has prescribed certain conditions for selling shares in an Offer-for-Sale (OFS) under IPO by significant shareholders and has extended anchor investors' lock-in period to 90 days, according to a statement issued by Sebi after its board meeting.

news.title: Court orders FIR against Terra Group for flat handover delay
news.para: Anu Bala (46), a resident of Roshanpura, had booked a flat in the residential project — Terra Casstle— on Alwar bypass road in Bhiwadi district of Rajasthan.
